WEBVTT

00:01.835 --> 00:04.515
MAN [ON TV]: We're at the federal
courthouse where Arthur Strauss...

00:04.671 --> 00:06.639
...will face the jury
on charges of kidnapping.

00:06.798 --> 00:07.970
This is an e-mail exchange...

00:08.132 --> 00:11.307
...between Clarke and FBI Director
Franklin. - This isn't Jeffrey.

00:11.470 --> 00:14.724
It's Clarke's e-mail. Time-stamped
and logged like it's been here all along.

00:14.890 --> 00:16.142
I miss you.

00:23.023 --> 00:26.823
Your Honor, we're having trouble
locating my next witness, Carrie Cooke.

00:28.487 --> 00:31.206
Carrie Cooke was murdered
along with her security team.

00:31.365 --> 00:32.992
- It's too late.
- Where's Strauss?

00:33.158 --> 00:35.286
SHEILA: He walked 20 minutes ago.
- Mike!

00:35.452 --> 00:36.544
[GUNSHOT]

00:36.703 --> 00:38.956
RYAN: It's Mark.
- Max, take Strauss to the car.

00:39.122 --> 00:40.920
MAX:
No. Mike. Mike. No. Unh!

00:41.708 --> 00:43.005
[DAISY GRUNTS]

00:44.211 --> 00:45.258
Get on your knees.

00:46.588 --> 00:48.181
Mike, stop. Don't do it.

00:53.679 --> 00:54.896
I know what I have to do.

00:58.600 --> 01:00.898
What took you so long?

01:12.531 --> 01:15.705
You're looking very well, Ryan.

01:15.867 --> 01:18.416
The suit, the grooming...

01:18.620 --> 01:20.622
...and you're back
with the Bureau full-time, yes?

01:20.789 --> 01:25.135
And you haven't fallen off the wagon.
Good for you.

01:26.503 --> 01:28.756
And yet there's something else about you.

01:28.922 --> 01:31.926
There's a lightness to you.

01:35.095 --> 01:37.348
Are you in love?

01:38.307 --> 01:39.354
Someone new?

01:39.558 --> 01:42.357
- Enough.
- You'll share...

01:42.561 --> 01:43.608
...eventually.

01:46.189 --> 01:48.237
What are you doing here, Ryan?

01:55.490 --> 01:57.367
This was a mistake. You can't help me.

01:57.534 --> 02:00.583
Oh, please, spare me the theatrics.
What's in the folder?

02:10.589 --> 02:12.262
Arthur Strauss is missing.

02:13.675 --> 02:18.431
Oh. Dear, oh, dear, you are in,
heh, such trouble.

02:18.597 --> 02:21.851
He's got no money. He's got no ID.
He can't have traveled far.

02:22.017 --> 02:25.112
He was last seen at the vicinity
of Red Hook in Brooklyn.

02:25.270 --> 02:28.319
- Where do you think he'd go?
- Why would I help you?

02:29.566 --> 02:31.864
- What are you offering?
- What do you want?

02:32.069 --> 02:36.540
You know, I have made my peace
with my predicament.

02:36.740 --> 02:37.957
But I'm concerned for you.

02:40.452 --> 02:44.423
I wonder if you are quite as prepared.

02:44.831 --> 02:47.926
- For what?
- Do I need to remind you, Ryan?

02:48.543 --> 02:52.013
When I die, you die.

02:54.174 --> 02:56.518
Don't worry about me, Joe.

02:56.968 --> 02:58.811
I'm gonna be just fine once you're gone.

02:59.054 --> 03:00.101
Mm.

03:00.972 --> 03:02.724
So you say.

03:03.934 --> 03:06.483
What do you want?

03:06.645 --> 03:09.489
- I want us back.
- "Us"? What "us"?

03:09.690 --> 03:10.907
Well, you and me.

03:11.108 --> 03:15.204
Bantering, laughing, shedding a few tears.

03:15.737 --> 03:22.040
I'd like for you to come
and visit me every day until D day.

03:22.202 --> 03:24.455
I think I deserve that much at least.

03:31.503 --> 03:34.097
You give me something on Strauss.

03:35.173 --> 03:37.722
If it pays off, I'll come back.

03:38.760 --> 03:39.977
Hmm.

03:42.013 --> 03:44.857
Well, what did I do when all hope was lost?

03:45.559 --> 03:49.735
I reached out to the good doctor.
He was my mentor and my ally.

03:49.896 --> 03:54.572
Someone can only assume
that he might do the same thing.

03:54.735 --> 04:01.209
You know, he touched a great many lives.
I suspect that he would lean on a...

04:01.366 --> 04:06.247
A friend in the neighborhood
in his hour of need.

04:10.000 --> 04:11.547
Tell me something, Ryan.

04:12.043 --> 04:13.966
Your dreams.

04:15.839 --> 04:17.307
Am I in them?

04:25.182 --> 04:26.650
[LOCK BUZZES]

04:37.027 --> 04:39.246
Hang on just one second.

04:43.867 --> 04:45.869
[VOMITING]

04:51.917 --> 04:53.919
[TOILET FLUSHING]

05:10.560 --> 05:12.437
- Hi.
- Hey.

05:15.273 --> 05:17.617
- Heh.
- Oh.

05:18.068 --> 05:21.163
- Well, I hope you feel better than you look.
- Not really.

05:23.240 --> 05:24.867
Hey, fill me in. What's going on?

05:25.033 --> 05:28.082
Well, the DOJ dropped their investigation
into us.

05:28.245 --> 05:31.124
Our cyber team was able to prove
the e-mail that Strauss' attorney...

05:31.289 --> 05:32.916
...claimed came from Clarke was a fake.

05:33.083 --> 05:36.087
- How did it get on the FBI server?
- I don't know. We're looking into that.

05:36.253 --> 05:39.132
But Bureau needed a fall guy,
so they suspended Gina.

05:39.339 --> 05:40.966
That's not fair. For how long?

05:41.174 --> 05:43.347
- Till after her hearing.
- We need to do something.

05:43.552 --> 05:47.273
I tried to take the bullet, but they
insisted it be hers since she was in charge.

05:47.430 --> 05:48.977
How's she taking it?

05:49.140 --> 05:50.858
She's not returning my calls.

05:55.814 --> 05:56.861
- Hey.
TOM: Hey.

05:57.023 --> 05:58.240
How's my girl?

05:58.400 --> 06:00.277
RYAN: Are you taking her home?
- Yeah.

06:00.443 --> 06:02.286
Make sure she stays in bed.

06:02.445 --> 06:04.868
- I'll stop by later.
- Thanks.

06:06.032 --> 06:07.705
(Hey.)'-

06:09.286 --> 06:10.333
Hey.

06:18.628 --> 06:21.632
How's Max doing? I left her messages.
I haven't heard back.

06:21.798 --> 06:24.096
- Don't hold your breath.
- We're still doing this?

06:24.259 --> 06:26.933
- You abandoned her.
- Last thing I wanted was for her to get hurt.

06:27.095 --> 06:28.221
Well, that's what happened.

06:28.388 --> 06:31.392
I could've ended Mark if you hadn't
interfered. Give me a break.

06:31.558 --> 06:35.608
I'm not gonna argue this with you. Strauss,
Mark, Daisy, they're still out there.

06:35.812 --> 06:38.986
So let's just focus on bringing them in.
All right?

06:41.318 --> 06:44.242
Before anyone asks, Mendez's replacement
has not been named yet.

06:44.446 --> 06:46.073
Now, anything on Mark Gray?

06:46.239 --> 06:49.163
Divers haven't recovered his body.
He couldn't have survived that fall.

06:49.326 --> 06:51.169
He's a cockroach. He survived.

06:51.328 --> 06:54.172
He's alive until we have a body.
Anything on Strauss and Daisy?

06:54.331 --> 06:58.211
No sightings. Running facial recognition
in real time on all video surveillance.

06:58.418 --> 07:02.844
Joe Carroll suggested that Strauss could
have a student nearby like Andrew or Kyle.

07:03.048 --> 07:06.018
Search the area where he escaped.
Look for anybody with a connection.

07:06.176 --> 07:07.894
It could be an ex-student, patient.

07:08.053 --> 07:10.476
We find who's helping him, we find Strauss.

07:18.563 --> 07:20.816
- You're still up?
- Hey.

07:21.858 --> 07:23.280
Yeah.

07:23.443 --> 07:26.162
- How was work?
- Brutal.

07:26.321 --> 07:29.245
Looks like you've been doing
some redecorating.

07:29.407 --> 07:31.034
How was seeing Joe?

07:31.576 --> 07:33.419
- Fine.
- Fine?

07:34.079 --> 07:37.128
- Yeah.
- Please don't treat me like an idiot.

07:37.666 --> 07:41.421
I'm sorry.
I just don't wanna get into it right now.

07:41.586 --> 07:43.930
Really? It looks like
you're pretty into it.

07:45.090 --> 07:47.809
- You just don't wanna get into it with me.
- Doc.

07:47.968 --> 07:51.347
You said I could ask you anything,
you'd give me real answer.

07:51.513 --> 07:53.186
So how was it seeing Joe?

07:54.641 --> 07:58.236
It was rough, but I handled it.

07:58.395 --> 08:00.773
What they said in court, the black ops?

08:00.939 --> 08:03.283
I did what I thought I needed to do
to get the job done.

08:03.483 --> 08:06.657
I made some mistakes,
but I'm seeing things more clearly now.

08:06.820 --> 08:08.447
I'm making better decisions.

08:09.030 --> 08:11.783
- You're holding back.
- I'm just...

08:13.493 --> 08:15.712
I don't wanna say any more.

08:15.870 --> 08:21.752
Because I don't wanna taint us with this.

08:21.918 --> 08:24.967
But if you wanna know more,
I'll tell you more.

08:25.130 --> 08:26.598
No more lies, Ryan.

08:28.049 --> 08:31.223
- If I can't trust you, I can't be with you.
- Okay.

08:31.386 --> 08:33.058
Okay.

08:35.432 --> 08:39.187
So tell me, what are you doing?

08:43.063 --> 08:47.786
I'm looking at these false IDs
that we recovered from the docks.

08:47.944 --> 08:49.491
I mean, they're impeccable.

08:49.654 --> 08:52.282
They're fully supported
with multiple public databases.

08:52.449 --> 08:55.749
Whoever did this was able to create
foolproof, three-dimensional identities.

08:55.910 --> 08:57.583
I've never seen anything like it.

08:57.746 --> 09:00.750
This is the same guy who planted
fake e-mails on the FBI server?

09:02.167 --> 09:06.388
Yeah. Strauss has some hacker genius
helping him.

09:54.260 --> 09:55.477
[SIGHS]

09:56.930 --> 09:58.307
[BELL DINGS]

10:31.548 --> 10:32.800
[DOOR OPENS]

10:35.426 --> 10:37.053
[CELL PHONE BUZZES]

11:01.244 --> 11:03.087
Who are you?

11:03.246 --> 11:05.749
THEO:
A friend of Dr. Strauss.

11:05.957 --> 11:08.460
Hey, I did what I was told.
I got his case thrown out.

11:10.378 --> 11:12.472
Okay, hold on, hold on.

11:12.672 --> 11:15.516
Wait. I am protected.

11:17.177 --> 11:18.520
All right, hold on.

11:19.721 --> 11:22.645
Wait, wait, please.
There's no need for violence.

11:24.475 --> 11:26.978
There's always a need for violence.

11:29.189 --> 11:30.441
No! Aah!

11:36.070 --> 11:39.665
- Guys, what do we got?
- We haven't found anyone with a connection.

11:39.824 --> 11:44.079
If one of Strauss' students is operating
in Red Hook, there has to be evidence.

11:44.245 --> 11:47.169
I looked at murder cases
in the tristate area. No leads.

11:47.498 --> 11:52.254
No. Not murder. Pull up missing-person
cases in the last 10 years.

11:52.420 --> 11:54.718
- Strauss' students are smart.
- Hmm.

11:54.881 --> 11:57.851
What better way of avoiding discovery
than not recovering a body at all?

11:58.009 --> 11:59.431
- Exactly.
- Got it.

11:59.594 --> 12:02.848
Okay. Now subtract out scofflaws
and runaways.

12:03.765 --> 12:07.895
Now, do any of these cases have in common
any towns or cities...

12:08.061 --> 12:10.359
...within a one-hour traveling radius
of Red Hook?

12:10.939 --> 12:13.909
- Hmm. Nothing.
- Try two hours.

12:14.067 --> 12:15.239
SLOAN:
Uh-huh.

12:16.694 --> 12:19.038
Beacon. In the Hudson River Valley.

12:19.197 --> 12:22.167
It's the last-seen location
for victims in six of the reports.

12:22.367 --> 12:24.527
Could be a hunting ground
for one of Strauss' students.

12:24.619 --> 12:28.044
- Strauss could have taken a boat to Beacon.
- It's a long shot.

12:28.206 --> 12:31.050
It's the only shot we have.
I'm gonna check it out.

12:31.251 --> 12:33.470
- Hey, I'm with you.
- No, that's not necessary.

12:33.670 --> 12:35.513
You said we should focus on the job.

12:35.672 --> 12:39.722
- Yeah.
- So let's focus. I'm with you.

12:48.434 --> 12:51.062
You should have called.
It'd have saved you the trip out.

12:51.229 --> 12:54.699
I've seen them both on TV,
but we haven't had any local sightings.

12:54.857 --> 12:58.953
I'm gonna need to see your missing-person
reports for the last 15 years.

12:59.112 --> 13:02.036
- I can pull that, sheriff.
- No, we're not pulling anything.

13:03.157 --> 13:06.001
You're that rogue agent from the news,
aren't you?

13:06.160 --> 13:07.958
"Ryan Hardy lies" and all that.

13:08.121 --> 13:10.544
Yeah. Well, don't believe everything
you see on TV.

13:10.707 --> 13:15.463
And yet here you are, acting like
you have no appreciation for protocol.

13:15.878 --> 13:19.473
I'm kind of pressed for time, sheriff.
I could really use your cooperation.

13:20.174 --> 13:21.391
Earn it.

13:22.010 --> 13:27.062
Six were reported missing in the last 10
years. They were all last seen here in Beacon.

13:29.475 --> 13:30.601
That's a coincidence.

13:31.227 --> 13:35.403
Or it's possible that Arthur Strauss
has an associate here.

13:35.565 --> 13:40.116
- I don't think so. Small town. I'd know.
- Hey, sheriff. May I?

13:41.362 --> 13:43.740
Remember that Jane Doe
we found in the marsh?

13:43.906 --> 13:48.002
She was missing fingers and teeth, so we
couldn't get an ID, but this could be her.

13:48.953 --> 13:52.173
- Do you have a suspect?
- We haven't gotten too far in that.

13:52.373 --> 13:54.842
- Show us where you found the body?
- I can do that.

13:59.881 --> 14:01.224
Keep me in the loop.

14:05.887 --> 14:10.643
I owe you an apology.
I've been distracted lately.

14:12.018 --> 14:14.737
Well, it seemed to coincide
with Mike coming back.

14:15.521 --> 14:20.402
No. That's not it.
It's the recent murders and the...

14:20.610 --> 14:24.410
- Everything brought up a lot of stuff for me.
- You sure?

14:25.323 --> 14:29.829
Feels like whenever I'm around the two
of you, there's unfinished business.

14:30.453 --> 14:32.831
No. Not at all.

14:35.583 --> 14:37.256
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

14:44.175 --> 14:47.850
- Oh, hey.
- Hi. I've come to check in on the patient.

14:48.012 --> 14:52.483
Good timing. I gotta get to work.
I'll see you later.

14:53.601 --> 14:54.944
Thanks.

14:56.020 --> 14:59.069
- How are you doing?
- Better. Yeah.

14:59.232 --> 15:01.951
Tom's been amazing.
He's too good to be true.

15:02.151 --> 15:05.576
Those are the ones you have to watch out
for. They're always hiding something.

15:07.323 --> 15:10.122
If anyone's hiding anything,
it's me, not Tom.

15:13.496 --> 15:16.750
Okay. Spill.

15:22.046 --> 15:24.890
I shouldn't have said anything. It's okay.

15:28.511 --> 15:29.933
[BEEPS]

15:30.096 --> 15:33.726
- Sure this is where you found the body?
- Absolutely. What does that thing do?

15:33.891 --> 15:38.021
It gives us an idea whether anything might
be buried here. I'm not finding anything.

15:38.229 --> 15:40.732
We searched this place.
I remember going home soaked.

15:40.940 --> 15:43.944
- Soaked?
HILARY: It was raining buckets that day.

15:45.695 --> 15:47.493
Is this area susceptible to flooding?

15:48.197 --> 15:49.244
Yeah.

15:50.700 --> 15:55.046
It's possible that the heavy rains dislodged
the body from where it was originally buried.

15:57.999 --> 16:00.468
Can you show us a path a body
could have taken to get here?

16:22.106 --> 16:23.153
Someone's been here.

16:36.162 --> 16:38.756
Looks like some kind of talisman.

16:38.915 --> 16:42.010
- Have you seen these before?
- No.

16:45.463 --> 16:47.591
What the hell is that?

16:49.383 --> 16:50.475
Hey. Hey!

16:50.635 --> 16:52.808
Stop! Stop!

16:52.970 --> 16:54.392
Stop right there!

16:55.848 --> 16:57.065
FBI!

17:04.732 --> 17:05.779
Where'd he go?

17:07.068 --> 17:09.069
HILARY:
I don't know.

17:09.654 --> 17:13.500
It's like he deliberately revealed himself.
Then when he was ready, he disappeared.

17:13.866 --> 17:15.539
What do you think he was doing?

17:17.703 --> 17:19.671
[BEEPS]

17:33.052 --> 17:34.099
[MACHINE BEEPS]

17:34.262 --> 17:36.014
Hey.

17:36.180 --> 17:37.477
I think I got something here.

17:56.367 --> 17:58.040
I think I got something here too.

18:01.205 --> 18:03.173
It's a burial ground.

18:06.544 --> 18:09.889
You've got nine victims, male and female.
Various ages and ethnicities.

18:10.089 --> 18:12.091
All killed during the past 10 to 15 years.

18:12.300 --> 18:16.021
The ID will take time.
The killer removed the teeth and fingers.

18:17.096 --> 18:21.317
I recognize that belt buckle from one of
the missing-persons reports you showed us.

18:22.226 --> 18:24.274
Look at that. She's right. One of ours.

18:24.478 --> 18:28.483
Okay, so this killer's been operating here
for 15 years without arousing any suspicion.

18:28.691 --> 18:29.943
Feels like one of Strauss'.

18:30.109 --> 18:33.579
Get us access to all local surveillance
video in the last 72 hours.

18:33.738 --> 18:36.867
Strauss is here. He's not getting away.

19:26.499 --> 19:27.842
[LOCK CHIRPS]

19:32.797 --> 19:34.094
[CELL PHONE CHIMES]

19:41.722 --> 19:44.441
I should be running that office.

19:44.600 --> 19:46.568
I hate them.

19:48.437 --> 19:50.485
I'm gonna get some sleep.

19:54.735 --> 19:57.363
[STATIC-X'S "GET TO THE GONE"
PLAYING ON STEREO]

19:59.573 --> 20:02.918
I fly, I fly around the world
Through the night sky

20:03.077 --> 20:05.705
I feel the end, the end is near
Relations die

20:05.871 --> 20:09.125
Killing the one thing I know this to be

20:13.671 --> 20:14.718
MAN:
Hi, Pat.

20:21.178 --> 20:24.398
Don't be scared.
We've been chatting online for months.

20:25.057 --> 20:26.434
Carl1988?

20:28.227 --> 20:30.355
How did you find me?

20:30.646 --> 20:34.742
We were on an encrypted site.
That's supposed to be anonymous.

20:38.028 --> 20:41.578
Don't you know
there's no such thing as anonymity online?

20:46.620 --> 20:48.372
[PAT GRUNTING]

20:50.624 --> 20:53.423
I know what you've been planning
for weeks.

20:53.627 --> 20:55.470
I'm gonna make real in the morning.

20:55.671 --> 20:58.515
Of course,
I'll be bouncing off the walls all night...

20:58.716 --> 20:59.933
...but I'm ready.

21:01.010 --> 21:03.104
Up. Don't worry.

21:03.304 --> 21:04.806
I'm not gonna steal your thunder.

21:05.014 --> 21:08.314
I'll make sure you get all the glory,
and no one will know I was here.

21:08.517 --> 21:10.144
Cool, right?

21:12.396 --> 21:14.649
[TYPES THEN SENDS TEXT MESSAGE]

21:21.906 --> 21:22.953
[ENGINE STARTS]

21:39.131 --> 21:40.474
So your uncle owns this place?

21:40.633 --> 21:43.933
Yeah. My parents were killed
in a crash when I was a kid.

21:44.512 --> 21:45.559
I'm sorry.

21:45.721 --> 21:49.726
It's all right. My uncle Duncan's
been making me dinner here ever since.

21:49.892 --> 21:52.987
- Today must have been tough for you.
- All right, forget tough.

21:53.854 --> 21:57.825
- Look, the odds are you know the killer.
- I still can't believe it's one of us.

21:57.983 --> 21:59.823
- Not thinking like a cop.
- Give her a minute.

22:01.320 --> 22:04.745
- It's obvious who the killer is.
- This is police business, Margo.

22:04.907 --> 22:07.751
It's town business when they start
pulling bodies out of the woods.

22:07.910 --> 22:10.504
- Who should we look at?
- Sheriff Windsor's no-good son, Justin.

22:10.704 --> 22:13.503
HILARY: Margo...
- There's something off about that boy.

22:13.707 --> 22:17.132
The sheriff does everything he can
to protect him. You know it's true.

22:17.294 --> 22:21.219
- I don't pay you to gossip.
- I'm helping with the police investigation.

22:21.382 --> 22:25.182
You really expect Hilary
to investigate her boss's son?

22:26.178 --> 22:29.182
So where does Justin live?

22:30.182 --> 22:33.061
It doesn't seem like your uncle
wants you to cross the sheriff.

22:33.227 --> 22:36.151
He worries about me.
He knows this job is difficult enough.

22:40.609 --> 22:42.202
I think this is Justin's.

22:42.361 --> 22:45.035
The fire is still smoking.
He couldn't have got far.

22:52.162 --> 22:54.915
Hey. What's that?

24:03.734 --> 24:04.781
Show your hands.

24:04.944 --> 24:07.038
- Right now.
- Justin, this is FBI. It's serious.

24:07.196 --> 24:09.198
RYAN: Show me your hands.
- I'll blow us up!

24:10.532 --> 24:15.914
I want you to put the lighter down
and slowly take a step towards me.

24:18.624 --> 24:20.251
[GRUNTS]

24:20.417 --> 24:22.920
Stupid, Justin. Real stupid.

24:23.128 --> 24:24.675
[JUSTIN GRUNTING]

24:25.923 --> 24:28.927
- Arthur Strauss. Where is he?
- I don't know.

24:29.134 --> 24:30.681
- I didn't kill anybody.
- Hey.

24:30.886 --> 24:33.139
We saw you in the woods today
wearing this mask.

24:33.973 --> 24:37.568
I wear it to chase off hikers, okay?
Keep them away from my setup.

24:37.726 --> 24:39.353
[CAR APPROACHING]

24:40.854 --> 24:42.447
- Who's here?
- I texted the sheriff.

24:43.232 --> 24:44.779
I had to. He's my boss.

24:49.947 --> 24:51.494
All right, I'm the boy's father.

24:55.744 --> 24:58.088
Dad, look what they did to me.

24:59.456 --> 25:01.299
Is it true?

25:01.792 --> 25:05.513
What Hilary said?
You've been making meth out here?

25:07.381 --> 25:08.428
I'm sorry.

25:09.842 --> 25:13.813
You know anything about this man
they're looking for? Arthur Strauss?

25:14.346 --> 25:17.350
I swear, I don't.

25:20.477 --> 25:23.447
Do you have anything to do
with those bodies they found?

25:25.899 --> 25:27.321
No.

25:29.069 --> 25:33.666
My son is troubled and plenty stupid.

25:33.824 --> 25:36.247
But I know when he's lying.
And he's telling the truth.

25:36.869 --> 25:39.543
Do you have any other questions for him?

25:40.914 --> 25:44.464
- No.
- Can I take him? I need to process him.

25:44.626 --> 25:46.299
JUSTIN: Dad.
- Now hold on a second.

25:46.462 --> 25:49.181
That's all right. Go ahead. Take him.

25:52.384 --> 25:55.103
Read him his rights in the car.

25:57.556 --> 26:01.356
- Why did you let him go?
- He's not smart enough to be one of Strauss'.

26:01.894 --> 26:04.317
[CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING
ON HEADPHONES]

26:18.911 --> 26:21.130
He's been gone for hours.
What if he's turned us in?

26:21.288 --> 26:24.417
Sweetheart, I promise you
he's loyal to me just like you.

26:24.625 --> 26:26.969
We should get out of here.
We're like sitting ducks.

26:27.169 --> 26:30.639
You wanna see if there are any pills
around here to take you down a few notches?

26:30.798 --> 26:32.766
[DOOR OPENS]

26:35.511 --> 26:36.933
As if on cue.

26:37.096 --> 26:38.268
We got problems.

26:40.099 --> 26:42.727
Ryan Hardy and the FBI are in town.

26:46.105 --> 26:49.200
[ON STEREO] Ooh, and it's all right
And it's comin' on

26:49.358 --> 26:52.988
We gotta get right back
To where we started from

26:53.153 --> 26:55.997
Love is good
Love can be strong

26:56.156 --> 27:00.002
We gotta get right back
To where we started from

27:00.160 --> 27:02.959
Ooh

27:06.834 --> 27:08.507
Do you remember the...?

27:23.892 --> 27:24.939
[GUN COCKS]

27:25.102 --> 27:27.104
[GUNFIRE & CROWD SCREAMING]

27:27.813 --> 27:31.363
Ooh, and it's all right
And it's comin' on

27:31.525 --> 27:34.699
We gotta get right back
To where we started from

27:34.862 --> 27:37.991
MICHELLE: At least four of the victims
were on your missing-persons list.

27:38.157 --> 27:40.000
- I'm still working on the rest.
- MO?

27:40.200 --> 27:43.500
Their killer is a Tin Man
searching for a heart.

27:44.663 --> 27:49.419
He inserts some type of tube into the chest
cavity and extracts the heart muscle.

27:49.585 --> 27:51.633
I've never seen anything like it.

27:51.795 --> 27:54.173
We found a 10th victim. She's an outlier.

27:54.381 --> 27:56.054
Female, mid-20s.

27:56.216 --> 27:58.776
- Killed approximately two decades ago.
- Tell me more about her.

27:58.886 --> 28:01.560
The heart-removal process
wasn't as surgical as the others.

28:01.722 --> 28:04.396
- He hadn't mastered it yet.
- Teeth and fingers removed...

28:04.558 --> 28:06.185
...but years after she was killed.

28:06.351 --> 28:08.854
Maybe he went back to the body
after he learned the technique.

28:09.021 --> 28:12.867
It could be his genesis victim. Someone
he had a personal relationship with.

28:13.025 --> 28:15.073
Let's prioritize identifying her.

28:15.235 --> 28:18.239
She could be our best shot
at finding the killer.

28:21.074 --> 28:22.576
STRAUSS:
Mm.

28:22.743 --> 28:26.919
You are a fine chef, Duncan.
This bacon is a revelation.

28:27.080 --> 28:28.753
Few folks know the joy of human flesh.

28:29.958 --> 28:32.086
- Wait, this isn't...?
- Oh, damn, girl, it's a joke.

28:33.962 --> 28:35.589
Your sense of humor sucks.

28:35.756 --> 28:38.885
I wonder what your heart
would look like in the palm of my hand.

28:40.093 --> 28:43.438
- Try me, sweetie.
- Children, behave.

28:43.597 --> 28:46.942
It's so rare
that I have my extended family together.

28:47.100 --> 28:48.943
Can't we get along?

28:49.561 --> 28:54.362
Dr. Strauss, now that you've slept
and eaten, shouldn't you be heading out?

28:55.484 --> 28:57.703
- Pardon?
- Well, I don't want you to get caught.

28:59.279 --> 29:02.283
I brought you cash from the diner.

29:02.866 --> 29:05.085
It should last you a few weeks.

29:05.619 --> 29:11.717
Well, thank you, son. But I feel safe here
in your fortress of solitude.

29:12.292 --> 29:13.885
But the FBI found my bodies.

29:14.044 --> 29:16.422
If you learned anything from me
over these years...

29:16.588 --> 29:18.932
...those bodies should
in no way lead them to you.

29:22.094 --> 29:23.721
What is it, Duncan?

29:23.887 --> 29:27.733
I killed before I met you,
before you taught me how to protect myself.

29:31.812 --> 29:36.443
Time is still on our side. We can't leave
until our new IDs and credit cards arrive.

29:37.317 --> 29:38.660
You reached out to him.

29:40.070 --> 29:42.869
You have no right to bring him here.
This is my home.

29:43.031 --> 29:44.749
Who's him?

29:45.575 --> 29:46.997
My best student.

29:47.160 --> 29:50.505
MAN [ON RADIO]: The FBI continues to
search for Arthur Strauss and Daisy Locke.

29:50.664 --> 29:54.840
Both are wanted for multiple murders and
should be considered extremely dangerous.

29:55.002 --> 29:56.882
WOMAN [ON RADIO]:
In a shooting in Providence...

29:57.045 --> 30:00.891
...a man wearing a mask entered an office
and opened fire, killing a dozen people.

30:01.049 --> 30:03.302
Police are reporting
the gunman is still at large...

30:03.468 --> 30:05.641
...and they believe he was stabbed
during the attack.

30:20.027 --> 30:24.123
You don't need that. I saw you come in
here. You look like you are in pain.

30:24.323 --> 30:27.372
I can help you. I'm a doctor.

30:29.328 --> 30:30.705
You can trust me.

30:31.872 --> 30:33.249
[LOCK CLICKS]

30:33.415 --> 30:36.134
You killed those people
in that office park.

30:36.293 --> 30:39.092
You're losing a lot of blood.
Looks like you nicked an artery.

30:39.296 --> 30:41.924
- Let me help you.
- Why? Why?

30:42.090 --> 30:46.971
Because I think fate
may have brought you to me.

31:00.525 --> 31:05.281
The need you have to take life...

31:05.447 --> 31:09.623
...the addiction to that high,
the power it gives you...

31:10.118 --> 31:11.665
...I have that too.

31:14.206 --> 31:16.049
I haven't met anyone like me before.

31:17.209 --> 31:19.211
I can hide you.

31:22.172 --> 31:23.924
- I need to finish.
- Whoa, whoa. whoa.

31:24.091 --> 31:26.435
- I need to finish.
- What is it that you need to do?

31:36.269 --> 31:38.021
Hey, Ryan.

31:39.064 --> 31:42.193
ME identified the genesis victim.
Her name is Fran Banks.

31:42.401 --> 31:45.200
- Sounds familiar.
- Married to Duncan, guy that owns the diner.

31:45.779 --> 31:48.373
- Hilary's uncle.
- He never reported her missing.

31:54.913 --> 31:59.043
Hey. Want some coffee? I'm bringing some
sandwiches down to the sheriff's office.

31:59.209 --> 32:03.214
- You're welcome to grab a booth if you like.
- Yeah. Yeah, we might do that.

32:06.383 --> 32:09.512
I hope you understand why I had to
call the sheriff last night. I hope...

32:09.970 --> 32:11.893
[DUNCAN GRUNTS & HILARY GASPS]

32:12.055 --> 32:15.275
Put your guns down
or I'm gonna slit my pretty niece's throat.

32:15.434 --> 32:17.778
- What's going on?
- He killed his wife. We found her body.

32:17.978 --> 32:19.651
- She's in California... Aah!
- Move.

32:19.813 --> 32:22.657
- We can work something out here.
- We sure can. Get out of the way.

32:22.816 --> 32:26.741
- I'm gonna walk out of here, get in my truck.
- We don't want you. We want Strauss.

32:26.903 --> 32:28.450
Give him to us and you walk.

32:28.613 --> 32:33.289
She's gonna bleed all over this floor unless
you put your guns down and let me walk out.

32:33.618 --> 32:35.165
[DUNCAN YELLS THEN GRUNTS]

32:42.836 --> 32:46.090
Strauss is the reason we caught you.
He brought us here. You know that.

32:46.256 --> 32:48.725
Why let him go free
when you're gonna be in prison?

32:48.884 --> 32:52.229
- Come on, just tell us where he is.
- Why would I tell you anything?

32:54.055 --> 32:55.978
So everything they're saying is true.

32:56.141 --> 32:58.894
How could you do that?
How could you kill all those people?

33:00.854 --> 33:05.075
Everything about you, about us, is a lie.

33:07.027 --> 33:09.029
What about my parents?

33:09.613 --> 33:11.832
Did you kill them too?

33:11.990 --> 33:13.742
Your mama was a squealer.

33:18.830 --> 33:20.707
Hey, hey, hey.

33:22.459 --> 33:25.838
This is the worst thing that'll
ever happen to you. But you're strong.

33:26.004 --> 33:27.631
And I know you can get through this.

33:27.797 --> 33:29.640
- I'm gonna get out of here.
- Hardy...

33:29.799 --> 33:31.767
- it's not a good time.
- I think I can help.

33:31.927 --> 33:35.898
My dad used to hunt with Duncan's dad.
There's this cabin in the woods they used.

33:36.056 --> 33:40.687
There's no road. You gotta hike in.
It'd be a good place to hide someone.

33:40.852 --> 33:42.525
- Can you get us there?
- I think so.

33:44.356 --> 33:46.734
- All right, let's go.
WESTON: Guys.

33:55.700 --> 33:57.794
[PAT GRUNTING]

34:02.332 --> 34:03.549
This is genius.

34:03.750 --> 34:06.720
You figured out a way to kill people,
and no one knows you exist.

34:06.878 --> 34:08.175
You done this before?

34:08.338 --> 34:11.842
- Yes, but this was my first mass murder.
- Impressive.

34:14.094 --> 34:17.688
You must never blame yourself
for your need to kill.

34:17.847 --> 34:19.895
You were born that way. Like a shark.

34:20.058 --> 34:23.402
And just like a shark,
you must stay beneath the water.

34:23.603 --> 34:25.731
- Like I've done here already?
- Yes, exactly.

34:25.897 --> 34:28.696
But you could have left him
in another location...

34:28.900 --> 34:31.779
...so you wouldn't have to rush back here
before the police.

34:32.404 --> 34:37.034
We need to match your injury
in case there are any witnesses.

34:38.952 --> 34:40.875
[PAT GRUNTING]

34:41.036 --> 34:43.005
[PAT SCREAMING]

34:45.375 --> 34:50.632
You have a second clown mask. Very good.
Hair fibers. DNA.

34:54.134 --> 34:55.636
[PAT SOBBING]

34:55.802 --> 35:01.434
Is there a way you like to kill?
Your own signature?

35:01.600 --> 35:07.858
I like the immediacy of a gun.
But the sound that a blade makes...

35:08.064 --> 35:11.068
...when it cuts into the
flesh is so delicious.

35:11.234 --> 35:12.656
Mm.

35:12.819 --> 35:17.871
The intimacy of strangulation
is such a rush.

35:19.909 --> 35:23.334
- Why limit myself?
- I don't suppose you have to.

35:24.039 --> 35:28.215
Yeah. I wanna master them all.

35:29.002 --> 35:33.553
What's your plan for Patrick's suicide?

35:33.715 --> 35:35.012
Gunshot wound to the head.

35:35.842 --> 35:37.094
Show me.

35:41.473 --> 35:43.100
- Just like that.
- Look in his eyes.

35:44.851 --> 35:50.028
There is something so special
in this moment...

35:50.190 --> 35:52.488
...when they know.

35:57.864 --> 35:59.241
[GUNSHOT]

36:00.116 --> 36:01.288
[GUN CLATTERS]

36:04.371 --> 36:05.497
STRAUSS:
Nicely done.

36:06.581 --> 36:09.835
You're ambitious. You'll be tempted
to have your moment in the sun.

36:10.001 --> 36:13.301
Others will even try to draw you
above the water.

36:13.713 --> 36:17.263
You mustn't let that happen.
You can't survive that way.

36:17.425 --> 36:22.306
There are so many things I can teach you.

36:23.181 --> 36:25.684
I'll never forget this.

36:26.851 --> 36:29.149
And I'll find a way to pay you back,
I promise.

36:31.147 --> 36:33.070
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

36:36.611 --> 36:37.658
Thank you for coming.

36:50.208 --> 36:52.176
I've missed our talks
since you've been away.

36:52.335 --> 36:55.054
Yes. Me too.

36:56.548 --> 36:59.552
Don't hover back there.

36:59.718 --> 37:01.720
- This is Daisy.
- Hi.

37:04.222 --> 37:06.395
You almost looked surprised
when you saw me.

37:06.558 --> 37:08.652
- Did you doubt I'd come?
- Of course not.

37:08.810 --> 37:11.780
- Mm.
- Thank you for everything you've done.

37:11.938 --> 37:15.863
The IDs,
planting that e-mail on the FBI server.

37:16.609 --> 37:17.906
I owe you my freedom.

37:18.611 --> 37:22.991
No, that's the least I could do.
You've... You've been like a father to me.

37:32.041 --> 37:33.463
[STRAUSS GAGGING]

37:33.626 --> 37:36.254
Which is why what you did
hurt me so much.

37:38.965 --> 37:40.717
[IN STRANGLED VOICE]
You owe me.

37:40.884 --> 37:42.557
Owe you?

37:43.011 --> 37:45.389
What you forced me to do, you exposed me.

37:45.930 --> 37:47.728
I don't owe you that.

37:50.769 --> 37:54.069
A father is supposed to sacrifice
for his children.

37:54.856 --> 37:59.908
Instead, you were willing
to sacrifice us all to save yourself.

38:08.161 --> 38:12.291
"A shark is supposed to stay
beneath the water."

38:14.959 --> 38:17.712
Isn't that what you said to me?

38:20.507 --> 38:22.475
He made do that.

38:25.220 --> 38:28.850
- You see that, right?
- Please. He blackmailed me too.

38:29.015 --> 38:32.440
He got my husband killed.
I won't tell anyone. I won't. Please.

38:32.602 --> 38:33.603
Please.

39:29.993 --> 39:31.711
Hello, Duncan.

39:31.870 --> 39:34.248
We found Strauss. Show him.

39:35.039 --> 39:38.418
His head was nearly severed from his body.
Who did that?

39:40.587 --> 39:42.430
That's not real.

39:42.630 --> 39:44.177
Trust me. It's real.

39:45.258 --> 39:49.308
- You killed him. You killed him.
- Take it easy.

39:49.470 --> 39:51.143
We didn't. Someone beat us to it.

39:51.306 --> 39:53.104
- Was it that bitch Daisy?
RYAN: Nope.

39:53.308 --> 39:56.437
She doesn't have the upper-body strength
to do that kind of damage.

40:01.107 --> 40:03.235
You'll never find him. He's a ghost.

40:05.445 --> 40:08.949
- What's his name?
- I don't know.

40:09.449 --> 40:13.670
All I know is that Strauss
called him his best student.

40:25.632 --> 40:27.100
[PLATES CLATTER]

40:29.636 --> 40:31.684
WOMAN:
Dad's home.

40:31.846 --> 40:33.018
[CHILDREN GIGGLE]

40:33.181 --> 40:36.560
Hey. And you let them stay up?

40:36.726 --> 40:39.445
They missed you.
You've been traveling so much.

40:39.604 --> 40:43.154
Oh, I've missed you guys too.
I missed you too.

40:43.316 --> 40:44.408
Mm.

40:44.567 --> 40:47.366
Please tell me
you don't have to go back on the road.

40:47.528 --> 40:50.998
I hope not, baby,
but when work calls, I gotta go.

40:51.199 --> 40:52.325
- Yeah.
THEO: Yeah.

40:52.492 --> 40:56.338
So did Mommy save me some dinner?
Yeah?

40:56.537 --> 40:57.629
- I did.
GIRL: Yeah.

40:57.789 --> 41:00.338
- Of course I did. Come on.
- All right.

41:01.292 --> 41:03.090
I'm gonna tickle you.

41:24.691 --> 41:26.159
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

41:34.534 --> 41:35.706
Hi, Mike.

41:35.868 --> 41:38.371
- What are you doing here?
- I'm sorry.

41:38.871 --> 41:40.418
Are you?

41:41.082 --> 41:45.053
What are you more sorry about? That I
was beat to hell or that Mark got away?

41:45.253 --> 41:47.005
If I could do things differently...

41:47.171 --> 41:50.220
You'd shoot Mark and plant the gun,
just like you did Lily.

41:51.926 --> 41:53.599
That was your plan, right?

41:54.387 --> 41:56.481
Wouldn't you rather see him dead
than alive?

41:56.639 --> 42:01.486
I'd rather never be forced to cover up
another one of your executions, Mike.

42:07.025 --> 42:08.026
Good night.

42:29.130 --> 42:31.053
MAX [ON COMPUTER]:
I 'd rather never be forced...

42:31.215 --> 42:33.593
...to cover up another one
of your executions, Mike.

42:50.610 --> 42:51.782
Ryan.

42:53.488 --> 42:54.956
You kept your promise.

42:56.282 --> 42:58.705
Who's Strauss' best student?

43:45.748 --> 43:47.750
[English - US - SDH]
